  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 845478c6a6e1ccb4b8830c60407f60cd, type: 3}
  m_Name: MCDialogue
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  npcName: Bread
  npcPortrait: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 6cef7fd6f7e0b7342815f144c89e3f8a, type: 3}
  prologueLines:
  - "I still remember the afternoons I spent at Grandma\u2019s restaurant when I
    was younger. After school, I\u2019d always go straight there, settling into the
    special seat\u2014the one where all her regulars sat. Grandma would always bring
    me my favorite dish. Nothing ever tasted better than her homemade chicken pot
    pie."
  - "I\u2019d sit there, waiting for Mom to finish work. When she arrived, she\u2019d
    join me, and we\u2019d eat together\u2014it was our little routine."
  - "Sometimes, other people would be seated at my table. Grandma always introduced
    me, encouraging me to chat with them. I\u2019d say hello, maybe share a few words,
    but I was usually too caught up in whatever I was doing to really get to know
    them."
  - "When I left for college, what I missed most wasn\u2019t just the food\u2014it
    was the warmth of the place, the feeling of home. But the hardest news came when
    I heard that Grandma was getting too sick to run the restaurant. She had no choice
    but to close it down."
  - "That day, I made a promise to myself: Once I graduate, I\u2019ll come back home
    and bring Grandma\u2019s restaurant back to life."
  restaurantLines:
  - "It felt like yesterday since I last came here. It\u2019s a whole lot barren
    though that\u2019s for sure."
  - Oh! Someone is at the door I should let them in.
  - She must be tired from today. I should go talk to her.
